SIMPLE: milepost
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milepost
<hw>Mile"post`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A post,
or one of a series of posts, set up to indicate spaces of a mile each or
the distance in miles from a given place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An event or accomplishment marking a significant
advance in an endeavor; a notable achievment; <as>as, putting a man in
orbit was a big <ex>milepost</ex> on the way to the moon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> milestone.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milesian</ent>⟦br⟧
